<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-12-01T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-12-01T08:00:00-05:00" n="907" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d907">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/3034</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Spain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WWB1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-12-01T13:00:00+00:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 1, 1916, 1 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 8.45 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>294. Understand that Swedish Government has approached neutral powers,
                            including United States, with a view to securing joint action on
                            questions affecting them. Am informed confidentially by French Embassy
                            that Spanish reply amounts practically to statement that Spain would
                            take only such action as England and France desired. French and British
                            Embassies consider Swedish proposals, which are apparently strongly
                            seconded by Switzerland, as clearly directed against Allies.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_WWB1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>